{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Renamed files appear in their own category and are not also counted as a deletion plus an addition.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is the real Git rename signal plus CLI categorization/output. A unit test over parsed fixtures can miss real rename detection behavior from Git on disk. Higher levels rejected: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because behavior text contains no AI/ML step, only deterministic CLI+Git processing.","test_description":"Create a real temp repo, commit a file, rename it, run the CLI as a subprocess, and assert stdout report has the file only under `renamed` with no corresponding `added`/`deleted` double count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Uses real filesystem + real git repo + real CLI subprocess; this would not be equivalent at Integration/Unit.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Diffs that include binary files do not cause the tool to crash; binary files are counted in the output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real binary diff behavior depends on Git output and subprocess execution; mocks can hide parsing/crash issues specific to actual binary patch metadata. Higher levels rejected: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no model output quality or multi-agent sequence exists.","test_description":"In a real temp repo, commit a binary file, modify it, run the CLI subprocess, and assert exit code is success and report includes binary file in counts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Requires real git binary diff format and process behavior.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.81,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Running the tool on a repository that has no commits yet produces an empty report rather than an error.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This failu